com.ibm.team.repository.client
Interface IContributorManager

public interface IContributorManager

A contributor manager for a particular team repository. The contributor manager provides operations for creating and updating contributor items in the repository. Contributors are a top-level item type that live outside the scope of any particular project.

Team repository objects are intended to be used by multi-threaded clients. Unless noted, the methods on ITeamRepository and its various subsidiaries, including IContributorManager, can be safely called from multiple threads concurrently without risk of corruption.

Since:
0.5

saveContributor

IContributor saveContributor(IContributor contributorWorkingCopy,
                             org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                             throws TeamRepositoryException
Creates or updates the given contributor in the repository. The item passed in must be a working copy whose properties values describe the new current state of the contributor in the repository. Returns the complete, shared item for the contributor. Subsequent changes must be made from a new working copy obtained from the resulting shared item. The working copy passed in is not affected, but cannot be reused.

Updating an existing item fails by throwing ItemNotFoundException if the item being updated does not exist.

The operation fails by throwing StaleDataException if the working copy is not based on the current state of the item in the repository at the time the server processes the save request. A client wishing to handle this mid-air collision should (1) re-fetch the current state of the item, (2) create a new working copy from it, (3) copy over changes from the old working copy, and (4) save the new working copy.

This operation generates a shared item event.

[Note: This operation should require repository admin permission. Revisit when the permission model is in place.]

Parameters:
contributorWorkingCopy - a working copy describing the new or updated contributor item; must not be null
monitor - a progress monitor, or null if progress reporting is not desired
Returns:
a complete, shared item for the contributor; never null
Throws:
NotLoggedInException - if the operation fails because the client was not logged in to the repository
ItemNotFoundException - if the item was not found
StaleDataException - if the working copy is not based on the current state of the item in the repository
TeamRepositoryException - if the operation fails for any other reason
org.eclipse.core.runtime.OperationCanceledException - if the operation is canceled. Cancelation can occur even if no progress monitor is provided.

updateContributorRecords

java.util.List updateContributorRecords(java.util.List contributorRecordsToSave,
                                        java.util.List contributorRecordsToDelete,
                                        org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                                        throws TeamRepositoryException
Creates, updates or deletes the given contributor records in the repository. The items to save passed in must be working copies whose property values describe the new current state of the contributor records in the repository. The handles to delete must be state handles. Returns the complete, shared items for the contributor records saved. Subsequent changes must be made from a new working copy obtained from the resulting shared items. The working copies passed in are not affected, but cannot be reused.

Updating or deleting an existing item fails by throwing ItemNotFoundException if the item being updated or deleted does not exist.

The operation fails by throwing StaleDataException if a working copy is not based on the current state of the item in the repository at the time the server processes the save request. A client wishing to handle this mid-air collision should (1) re-fetch the current state of the item, (2) create a new working copy from it, (3) copy over changes from the old working copy, and (4) save the new working copy.

This operation generates a shared item event.

Parameters:
contributorRecordsToSave - a list of working copies describing the new or updated contributor record items; null if none.
contributorRecordsToDelete - a list of state handles describing the contributor record items to delete; null if none
monitor - a progress monitor, or null if progress reporting is not desired
Returns:
a list of complete, shared items for the contributor records saved; never null
Throws:
NotLoggedInException - if the operation fails because the client was not logged in to the repository
ItemNotFoundException - if an item was not found
StaleDataException - if a working copy is not based on the current state of the item in the repository
TeamRepositoryException - if the operation fails for any other reason
org.eclipse.core.runtime.OperationCanceledException - if the operation is canceled. Cancellation can occur even if no progress monitor is provided.

deleteContributor

void deleteContributor(IContributorHandle contributorHandle,
                       org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                       throws TeamRepositoryException
Deletes the given contributor item from the repository including both the current and previous states. Upon successful completion, the item and all its states will no longer be visible in the repository. The delete operation has no effect if the item has already been deleted but will fail if the item does not exist. Note that the delete operation may result in dangling references to the deleted item.

This operation generates a shared item event if the item manager knows about the item being deleted.

[Note: This operation should require repository admin permission. Revisit when the permission model is in place.]

Parameters:
contributorHandle - the handle of the contributor to be deleted; must not be null
monitor - a progress monitor, or null if progress reporting is not desired
Throws:
NotLoggedInException - if the operation fails because the client was not logged in to the repository
ItemNotFoundException - if the item was not found
TeamRepositoryException - if the operation fails for any other reason
org.eclipse.core.runtime.OperationCanceledException - if the operation is canceled. Cancellation can occur even if no progress monitor is provided.

                                                    org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                                                    throws TeamRepositoryException
Fetches a contributor record by one of its identities.

Parameters:
identity - an identity of the contributor record we are trying to fetch; must not be null
flags - bit-wise OR of the constants declared on the IItemManager interface; specify IItemManager.DEFAULT to get a shared item (recommended) that tracks the current state of the item; specify IItemManager.REFRESH to ensure that the shared item is up-to-date; specify IItemManager.UNSHARED to return the current state of the item not as a shared item (and without affecting the shared item if one exists).
monitor - a progress monitor, or null if progress reporting is not desired
Returns:
a complete contributor record object; never null

                                                   org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                                                   throws TeamRepositoryException
Fetches the contributor records by one of their identities.

Parameters:
identities - The list of identities of contributor records we are trying to fetch; must not be null
flags - bit-wise OR of the constants declared on the IItemManager interface; specify IItemManager.DEFAULT to get shared items (recommended) that track the current state of the items; specify IItemManager.REFRESH to ensure that the shared items are up-to-date; specify IItemManager.UNSHARED to return the current state of the items not as shared items (and without affecting the shared items if they exist).
monitor - a progress monitor, or null if progress reporting is not desired
Returns:
a list of ContributorRecords corresponding to the identities passed in with null elements corresponding to identities that aren't found; never null.
Throws:

fetchAllContributors

java.util.List fetchAllContributors(org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                                    throws TeamRepositoryException
Retrieves all contributors in this repository. The resulting items are complete (have all their properties), and are shared items that track the current item changes.

Since the results are shared items, a call to this operation may generate item manager events (dependent on which contributors the item manager already knows about).

Items returned by this method will have their origin set to the repository associated with this manager.

Parameters:
monitor - a progress monitor, or null if progress reporting is not desired
Returns:
a list of complete, shared items for contributors (element type: IContributor); items are in no particular order; list itself is never null
Throws:
NotLoggedInException - if the operation fails because the client was not logged in to the repository
TeamRepositoryException - if anything goes wrong
org.eclipse.core.runtime.OperationCanceledException - if the operation is canceled. Cancellation can occur even if no progress monitor is provided.
